1. rwkv7_fast.cu — fused fp16 decode GEMV
-----------------------------------------
Derived from: faster3a_2605/cuda/rwkv7_v3a_ops.{cu,cpp}
  (`linear_orig_row1_exact4_f16_kernel`).
Modifications:
  * Extracted ONLY the row-1 exact GEMV (`gemv_m1`) into a standalone extension with
    no cublasLt / WMMA dependency. It replaces the r/k/v/o + ffn projection GEMVs on
    the M==1 (bsz1) decode path, opt-in via RWKV_FAST_LINEAR=1 (default off). No LoRA
    kernel is vendored (the LoRA down/up projections use sglang's own ReplicatedLinear).
  * fp32-accumulate; built WITHOUT --use_fast_math (IEEE arithmetic, no FTZ / approx
    transcendentals). Deterministic per-block reduction (no cross-block atomic).


2. rwkv7_sparse_cmix.cu — sparse sqrelu FFN value-projection
-----------------------------------------------------------
Derived from: faster3b_2606/cuda/rwkv7_mega_ops_260602.cu
  (`cmix_sparse_down_relu_one_vtile_hfma2_split2_kernel`).
Modifications:
  * Kept albatross's per-tile ballot/popc compaction of the nonzero relu(k)^2 rows
    (which skips ~9/10 of the value-weight reads); wired opt-in via RWKV_SPARSE_FFN=1
    (default off) for the M==1 (bsz1) decode path.
  * Replaced albatross's half2 hfma2 accumulation with fp32 register accumulation +
    an fp32 output buffer; the kernel takes the RAW key preactivation and applies
    relu()^2 itself (fusing the square into the load).
  * Accuracy: skipping exact-zero rows is bit-exact; the cross-inter-tile combine uses
    a float atomicAdd (order-nondeterministic to ~1 ULP, cuBLAS split-K class — not a
    run-to-run bit guarantee). Passes the greedy-EXACT + verify_batch gates.


Verification of both: bench/verify_{m1d,batch,fast_linear,sparse_cmix}.py
(0.1B/1.5B/7.2B, cuda-graph). Honest gains + design in docs/design/m6-sparse-ffn.md,
docs/findings/0015. The WKV recurrence itself is our own kernel (wkv_recurrent.py, not
in this dir) and keeps fp32 state.
